The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 BRIEFS

 Krishnagar, July 15: Madhu Sarkar, 40, a milk trader, was hacked to death by his 22-year-old cousin after being fined by a village shalishi (conciliation meeting) for having an affair with Madhus wife.

 Police said Bhola Sarkar, also a milk trader, broke the wall of Madhus home with a hammer on Saturday night and killed him with a sickle in front of his wife and child-ren, aged 8 and 6.

 Bolpur: Police on Saturday found 27 fake currency notes of Rs 500 denomination on a man from Jharkhand. Abdul Kader had given the fake notes to a trader after buying rice from him at Hattala here, about 190km from Calcutta. He has been arrested. 

 Barasat: The BSF has seized red sandalwood worth around Rs 3 crore from three traders at Swarupnagar in North 24-Parganas. Officials said the three were planning to export the sandalwood, which is banned.




